FinishedEventObserver  
 

Class Summary
BreadthFirstGraphSearch Breadth First Search(BFS) is one of the simplest algorithms for searching a graph, given a graph and a source vertex (s), BFS systematically explores the edges of G to discover every vertex that is reachable from s.
DepthFirstSearch Searches deaper in the graph whenever possible.
StronglyConnectedComponents Finds the strongly connected components in a given directed graph A strongly connected component of a directed graph G=(V,E) is a max set of vertices C such that for every pair of vertices u and v in C u is reachable from v and v is reachable from u.
TopologicalSort DAG or a directed acyclic graph is a directed graph with directed cycles.
TransposeGraphService Used to transpose a directed graph
 

Enum Summary
Color Used in Graphs algorithms such as BFS or DFS
